t 1235","about 1225":"about 1225","West Linton, Peeblesshire, Scotland":"West Linton, Peeblesshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland, United Kingdom","Roxburghshire, Scotland":"Roxburghshire, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Rutherford","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish and northern English: habitational name from Rutherford in Maxton (Roxburghshire), apparently named with Old English <i>hrīther</i>, <i>hrȳther</i> ‘ox’ + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’, though a British Celtic origin of the type <i>ro-</i> ‘great’ + <i>dubr-</i> ‘water, river’ is also possible for the first element. Places named <i>Rutherford</i> in West Linton (West Lothian) and Barningham (North Yorkshire) are less likely sources of the name."],"variants":[{"name":"Reliford","meanings":["Altered form of English   Rutherford  . Its bearers are mainly African Americans. Compare   Relaford  ,   Releford  ,   Relford  ."]},{"name":"Retherford","meanings":["Altered form of English   Rutherford  ."]}]},{"name":"Nichol","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a common medieval vernacular form of   Nicholas .  In modern use, except in Scotland where it is still bestowed mainly on boys, it is found more frequently as a girl's name, possibly being taken as a variant of   Nicole ."],"variants":[{"name":"Nicoll","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Nicol ."]},{"name":"Nicholl","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Nicol ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Nichol de Rutherford was born about 1204, in Roxburghshire, Scotland, his father, Hugh de Rutherfoord, was 26 and his mother, Mrs Hugo Rutherford, was 17. He had at least 3 sons and 1 daughter with Euphemia De Lisle. He died after 1283."},"et":{"abt. 1204–aft. 1283":"umbes 1204–pärast 1283","1204–1283":"1204–1283","1200–1264":"1200–1264","1225–1293":"1225–1293","1235–1300":"1235–1300","1236–Female":"1236–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1180–1252":"1180–1252","1189–Female":"1189–Surnud","abt. 1204":"umbes 1204","1264":"1264","1252":"1252","1283":"1283","aft. 1283":"pärast 1283","1293":"1293","1180":"1180","1204":"1204","1236":"1236","about 1209":"umbes 1209","1225":"1225","1235":"1235","1300":"1300","1189":"1189","1200":"1200","about 1235":"umbes 1235","about 1225":"umbes 1225","West Linton, Peeblesshire, Scotland":"West Linton, Peeblesshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Roxburghshire, Scotland":"Roxburghshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"abt. 1204–aft. 1283":"noin 1204–1283 jälkeen","1204–1283":"1204–1283","1200–1264":"1200–1264","1225–1293":"1225–1293","1235–1300":"1235–1300","1236–Female":"1236–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1180–1252":"1180–1252","1189–Female":"1189–Kuollut","abt. 1204":"noin 1204","1264":"1264","1252":"1252","1283":"1283","aft. 1283":"1283 jälkeen","1293":"1293","1180":"1180","1204":"1204","1236":"1236","about 1209":"noin 1209","1225":"1225","1235":"1235","1300":"1300","1189":"1189","1200":"1200","about 1235":"noin 1235","about 1225":"noin 1225","West Linton, Peeblesshire, Scotland":"West Linton, Peeblesshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Roxburghshire, Scotland":"Roxburghshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"abt. 1204–aft. 1283":"environ 1204–après 